Program 4 — Build and Run Java Application with Maven and Migrate to Gradle
Aim

To build and run a Java application using Maven and migrate the same application to Gradle.

Step 1 — Create Maven Project

Open Command Prompt:

mkdir program4
cd program4

Create Maven project:

mvn archetype:generate -DgroupId=com.example -DartifactId=maven-example -DarchetypeArtifactId=maven-archetype-quickstart -DinteractiveMode=false

Navigate project folder:

cd maven-example
Step 2 — Configure pom.xml
<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0
         http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd">

    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>

    <groupId>com.example</groupId>
    <artifactId>maven-example</artifactId>
    <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>

    <dependencies>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>junit</groupId>
            <artifactId>junit</artifactId>
            <version>4.12</version>
            <scope>test</scope>
        </dependency>
    </dependencies>

    <build>
        <plugins>

            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
                <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>
                <version>3.8.1</version>

                <configuration>
                    <source>1.8</source>
                    <target>1.8</target>
                </configuration>

            </plugin>

        </plugins>
    </build>

</project>
Step 3 — Create App.java

Path:

src/main/java/com/example/App.java
package com.example;

public class App {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        System.out.println("Hello, Maven");

        System.out.println("This is the simple realworld example....");

        int a = 5;
        int b = 10;

        System.out.println(
                "Sum of " + a + " and " + b + " is " + sum(a, b)
        );
    }

    public static int sum(int x, int y) {
        return x + y;
    }
}
Step 4 — Build and Run Maven Project

Build project:

mvn clean install

Run project:

mvn exec:java -Dexec.mainClass="com.example.App"
Maven Output
Hello, Maven
This is the simple realworld example....
Sum of 5 and 10 is 15
Step 5 — Migrate Maven Project to Gradle

Run:

gradle init

Select:

Generate Gradle build from Maven → yes
Build Script DSL → 2 (Groovy)
New APIs → no
Step 6 — Configure build.gradle
plugins {
    id 'java'
}

group = 'com.example'
version = '1.0-SNAPSHOT'

repositories {
    mavenCentral()
}

dependencies {
    testImplementation 'junit:junit:4.12'
}

task run(type: JavaExec) {
    main = 'com.example.App'
    classpath = sourceSets.main.runtimeClasspath
}
Step 7 — Build and Run Gradle Project

Build project:

gradlew build

Run project:

gradlew run
Gradle Output
Hello, Maven
This is the simple realworld example....
